1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 Be7 6. Bg2 O-O 7. O-O Nbd7 8.
Qc2 c6 9. Rd1 b6 10. b3 Ba6 {This is more active than 10...Ba6 and forces
White to deviate from the natural course of events.} 11. Bc1 $5 {One of the
most paradoxical Catalan moves I have ever seen. It is a recent try bringing
some new life into this line. White actually loses a tempo to regroup with the
bishop to b2, relying on the fact that the a6-bishop is vulnerable in many
lines. Obviously, ...Ba6-b7 would transpose to the normal closed lines below.}
({Usually White tries correcting his bishop's position in another way:} 11. Bf4
Nh5 {(unfortunately not forced)} 12. Bc1 Nhf6 13. Bb2) ({Or else he can try
making use of the bishop on the actual square with} 11. a4) 11... Rc8 12. Bb2
Ne4 ({The main alternative is} 12... c5 13. Nc3 $1 Bb7 {simply returns the
extra tempo.} ({The point is that Black has insufficient control on d5:} 13...
dxc4 14. d5 exd5 15. Nxd5 Nxd5 16. Rxd5 Bb7 17. Rd2 Qc7 (17... cxb3 18. axb3
$16 {attacks a7 and leaves the d7-knight under a dangerous pin.}) 18. bxc4 $14)
14. Ne1 $5 {Pinning the d5-pawn and increasing the pressure on it.} (14. cxd5
cxd4 $132 {Wojtkiewicz,A (2460)-Ostrowski,L (2380) Warsaw 1989 (1-0, 30)})
14... cxd4 (14... Ba8 15. cxd5 cxd4 16. dxe6 dxc3 17. exd7 Rc7 18. Bxc3 Bb4 19.
Bxb4 Rxc2 20. Nxc2 $16) 15. Rxd4 Bc5 16. Rdd1 $14 {with a pleasant Catalan
position.}) (12... Bb7 13. Nc3 {once again transposes to normal lines}) 13. Nc3
Nxc3 {Looks like a small concession.} (13... f5 14. e3 Nxc3 (14... Bd6 15. a4
$36) (14... Bb7 15. Ne2 Bd6 16. Nf4 Qe7 17. Ne5 $14) 15. Qxc3 Bb7 16. Ne1 Bd6
17. Nd3 Qe7 $14) 14. Qxc3 Bd6 (14... Bb7 15. Qd3 {/\e2-e4.} f5 16. Qe3 Rf6 17.
Ne1 $14) 15. Qc2 f5 (15... c5 16. e4 cxd4 17. Nxd4 dxc4 18. Nxe6 fxe6 19. Rxd6
$16) 16. e3 (16. a4 $1 Bb7 17. a5 $14 {poes more problems.}) 16... Bb7 17. Rac1
Qe7 18. Ne1 a5 19. Nd3 $14 {Both sides have a normal position but White's is
preferable as he controls all the important squares and has more space, Ding,
L (2783)-Zhigalko, S (2635) Khanty-Mansiysk 2017 (½-½, 41).} *

