Gupta,A (2607)-Ahlander,B (2416) Reykjavik 2017 (1-0, 50)}) 14. Nxd4 b5 (14...
Bc5 {does not bring much positive as the e7-square is not safe for the queen.}
15. Ne3 dxc4 16. bxc4 Qc7 17. Qa4 Bxd4 18. Rxd4 Nc5 19. Qd1 Bb7 20. Nd5 Nxd5
21. cxd5 $16 {Baumgartner,U (2338)-Jirk,J (2338) ICCF email 2002 (½-½, 23)
With two strong bishops and a dangerous central pawn.}) 15. Ne3 bxc4 16. Ndf5 {
White has overwhelming activity and retrieving the pawn is a matter of time.
Still, some accuracy is needed in order to maintain the advantage intact.} Bc5
(16... Re8 17. Nxd5 Nxd5 18. Bxd5 $16) 17. b4 $5 {Forcing the bishop onto an
exposed square.} Bxb4 (17... Bb6 18. Qc3 $16) (17... Bxe3 18. Bxe3 $16) 18. Qa4
