24. Nxd5 $18) 19. Qxa5 Bxa5 20. Ne7+ Kh8 21. Nxc8 Rxc8 22. Nxd5 c3 23. Nxf6
Nxf6 24. Rd6 Be2 25. Be3 Bb4 26. Rc6 Rxc6 27. Bxc6 c2 (27... a5 28. Rc1 $18 {
wins the awn soon.}) 28. Bxa7 $16 {Matheis, T (2397)-Polakovic, P (2445) ICCF
email 2009 (1-0, 73) due to the far advanced pawn the technical process of
